@qjhart

[ReadMe](https://github.com/ucd-library/glm-lightning/blob/main/README.org) describes units of `lat` and `lon` as reproduced below.

```
    flash_lat:units = "degrees_north" ;

    flash_lon:units = "degrees_east" ;

    flash_area:units = "m2" ;
```


In the NCL file, these are subsequently assigned to `lat`, `lon`, and `area` variables for `flashes.csv`.

      lat=fin->flash_lat, etc.

However, the values of `lat` and `lon` in flashes.csv do not agree with polar coordinates. 

Based on our discussion, these are perhaps Albers equal area projections. If that is true, what values of standard parallels and origin are considered for this conversion? We can modify the description on the repo accordingly too.

