The way you handle the API response and update the HTML is pretty much the same as what's done in the `handleCitySearch` function, so it would be better if you could use the same function in both places, like:

```js
function handleCurrentTemp(response) {
  let lat = response.coords.latitude;
  let lon = response.coords.longitude;
  let url = `https://api.shecodes.io/weather/v1/current?lon=${lon}&lat=${lat}&key=${apiKey}&units=metric`;

