## 🐛 Bug Report
<!-- Provide a clear description of what the bug is -->

Hi! Until recently, ESMValTool was pinned in a way that we used iris 3.2.1. This has recently been changed (see https://github.com/ESMValGroup/ESMValTool/issues/2945) so that we could use iris 3.4.0 in our environment for a development installation of ESMValTool. After running some recipes using iris 3.4.0, I noticed that some of our CMORized OBS data files (CMIP5-like standards) could not be loaded with iris any more due to `cell_method` issues. It looks like our files are missing some information, e.g. `ts:cell_methods = "time" ;` but such files could be loaded with iris 3.2.1. 

## How To Reproduce
Steps to reproduce the behaviour:

Assuming access to Jasmin:

1. Load the cube

```python
import iris
import.iris("/gws/nopw/j04/esmeval/obsdata-v2/Tier2/HadISST/OBS_HadISST_reanaly_1_Amon_ts_187001-201712.nc")
```

## Expected behaviour
<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen -->
Cube successfully loaded

